    "Name": "King Crabrauder",
    "Details": "After launching a series of retaliatory raids against the Lyran Alliance as punishment for stealing the Light Engine plans from them, Wolfs Dragoons wound up finding a sizable cache of intact King Crab arms but without the corresponding torsos and legs. Unwilling to waste such a windfall, the Dragoon's kept them in storage in hopes of finding a use for them later. After the destruction of the Jihad, Wolfs Dragoons contracted Irian BattleMechs Unlimited to make use of those arms by attaching them to reworked Marauder II torsos and legs. The resulting mech was then fitted with extensive Clan-spec equipment to produce this unusual design. The 1D configuration builds on the 1C by replacing the Gauss Rifles with HAG30s for maximum firepower while keeping the twin ER PPCs and LRM 15s.<br><br>S-class mechs feature upgrades to their armour, thermal management and defensive systems that substantially improve their survivability on the 31st century battlefield.",
